# ViewModel State Pattern

Every ViewModel must expose:

- State (`StateFlow`)
- Events (`SharedFlow`)
- Actions (sealed interface/class)

Pattern:

    import com.degustor.app.core.ui.UiText

    data class UserUiState(
        val loading: Boolean = false,
        val users: List<User> = emptyList(),
        val error: UiText? = null
    )

    sealed interface UserUiAction {
        data object Load : UserUiAction
    }

    sealed interface UserUiEvent {
        data class ShowMessage(val value: UiText) : UserUiEvent
    }

Rules:

- expose immutable `StateFlow` and `SharedFlow`
- keep mutable flows private
- ViewModel handles presentation logic and screen state
- ViewModel must not call API or repository directly
- ViewModel should depend on use cases for business logic
- ViewModel may depend on other presentation-safe abstractions when justified
- use `UiText` for user-facing messages in state and events
- only use raw `String` for non-UI data or intentionally dynamic backend content
